name: Hotel Anantashram

reviews.review_text: Absolute favourite. Every single preparation is mind-blowing. Was so happy to take my husband here and have him taste what I grew up with. The taste hasn't changed in years now. Such fond memories and such a wonderful experience. Staff treat you like family!

First time tried Goan Thali. Going to Anantashram was a right decision. It was closer to where we stayed. Ordered special prawn meals, vow it was really delicious. Crab curry was awesome. Every dish served in the thali was wonderful. Prawn moilee as side dish for roti was wonderful combination. Goan Fizz was a great mocktail, I've not had such taste of cocounut milk and tender coconut water mix. Everything tasted home made without any masala and dishes are made with coconut milk. Overall worth visit and pocket friendly too

Been visiting this place for many years , best place to have a Goan fish curry rice . Food is wonderfully cooked , with you being received right at entrance by the ever smiling owner Sripad  Shetye , he really greets you well and sees to that all his customers are well attended to .

description:
**Embark on a Culinary Journey at Hotel Anantashram**

Nestled in the scenic surroundings of Naval Base Verem, Hotel Anantashram shines brightly with an impressive rating of 4.1 stars from over 5,300 enthusiastic reviews. This beloved dining spot is a treasure trove for seafood lovers, boasting specialties such as seafood, fish thali, and their highly praised kingfish dishes. Along with an extensive selection of liquors, it's easy to see why this restaurant has garnered such a loyal following.

**A Warm & Inviting Ambiance**

Upon entering Hotel Anantashram, guests are greeted by an atmosphere that radiates warmth and familiarity. Influenced by Goan culture, the restaurant features a cozy décor with rustic wooden elements and vibrant hues that reflect local artistry. Gentle lighting creates an inviting space for diners, while the cheerful background music adds a lively touch to the overall experience. Images of the restaurant showcase its charming interiors, with colorful adornments and a welcoming dining area that captures the essence of a family gathering.

**A Culinary Feast to Remember**

The menu at Hotel Anantashram is a delightful homage to Goan cuisine, featuring signature dishes that have captivated patrons for years. Their Goan fish curry rice is a perennial favorite, showcasing the restaurant's commitment to freshness and flavor. With customer reviews highlighting dishes like the special prawn meal and crab curry, it’s evident that each plate is crafted with care and authenticity. The extravagant fish thali, beautifully presented with an array of vibrant accompaniments, is a must-try for first-time visitors. The Prawn Moilee, noted for its coconut milk base, complements the roti perfectly and is an exemplary representation of homemade flavors. 

For those looking to quench their thirst, the Goan Fizz (a delightful mix of coconut milk and tender coconut water) has received rave reviews for its refreshing taste—a true local treat that mirrors the vibrancy of Goa.

**Exceptional Service Like No Other**

One of the standout features at Hotel Anantashram is the genuine hospitality extended by the staff. From the moment you step inside, you are welcomed by the ever-smiling owner, Sripad Shetye, who ensures that every guest feels like part of the family. The attentive service, paired with the traditional Goan culinary experience, creates an environment where everyone is made to feel at home. The restaurant accommodates both walk-ins and reservations, making it accessible for spontaneous visits as well as planned outings.

**A Resounding Popularity Among Diners**

Hotel Anantashram has established itself as a go-to destination for anyone craving authentic Goan cuisine. The restaurant's reputation extends beyond just local patrons, with numerous reviews praising its consistent quality and nostalgic flavors. Social media buzz highlights its community-focused approach and the joy of sharing long-held family favorites. Customers frequently share memories of their experiences, reinforcing the restaurant's position as both a culinary and social hub.

**Visual Indulgence**

The photos shared by patrons speak volumes about the culinary artistry and ambiance presented at Hotel Anantashram. One can truly appreciate the vibrant presentation of the thali and mouth-watering seafood dishes captured in the images. The inviting atmosphere comes through visually as the warm lighting and rustic decor encourage a relaxed dining experience.

In summary, Hotel Anantashram is not just a restaurant; it's a culinary destination steeped in tradition and heartfelt hospitality. With its commitment to quality seafood, welcoming environment, and the charm of Goan culture, it's clear that this restaurant has earned its reputation as a cherished culinary landmark. Whether you are a local or a traveler, a visit to Hotel Anantashram promises to be a delightful experience, bursting with flavor and warmth.
